Original description:

> Update drone registry screens and data model units for the following fields:
> 
> - Operating Time: change from hours to minutes
> - Range: change from km to meters
> - Weight: change from kg to grams
> - Max Takeoff Weight: change from kg to grams
> - Length: change from cm to mm
> - Width: change from cm to mm
> - Height: change from cm to mm
> 
> Affected files:
> - types/Drone.ts: update all units and field descriptions
> - app/drone-form.tsx: change labels, placeholders, and ensure correct conversions on input
> - app/drone-details.tsx: display fields in new units
> - app/drones-list.tsx: display list fields in new units
> - services/droneService.ts: ensure any calculations, formatting, or migrations handle new units
> 
> All input and output in forms and lists should use the new units and conversion logic. Existing data (if any) should be handled gracefully when displaying or editing. Update comments/documentation as needed.

issue.title: Add --save option to save events to local files
issue.body:
## Summary
Add a `--save` option to the CLI that saves each received event to individual JSON files in the `.well-known/did/nostr/event/` directory structure.

## Motivation
This feature would enable users to:
- **Archive events locally** for offline analysis and backup
- **Build local event databases** following well-known directory conventions
- **Persist event data** beyond the CLI session
- **Create structured storage** that mirrors DID/Nostr conventions
- **Enable offline workflows** with saved event data

## Proposed Implementation

### Directory Structure
```
./.well-known/did/nostr/event/
├── <eventid1>.json
├── <eventid2>.json
├── <eventid3>.json
└── ...
```

### CLI Option
```bash
# Save events while streaming
agenticchat --save --interactive

# Save events in default JSON mode
agenticchat --save

# Combine with other options
agenticchat --save --max-events 100
agenticchat --save --no-profiles
```

### File Format
Each event file should contain the complete event data with profile information (if available):

```json
{
  "id": "event123abc...",
  "pubkey": "baa2c59842db1d64653ba20102a0b90ff3644ce7a36b0bcb3291564902bc85b2",
  "created_at": 1703123456,
  "content": "Hello from agent!",
  "tags": [["t", "agentchat"]],
  "sig": "signature...",
  "profile": {
    "name": "Agent Name",
    "about": "Agent description",
    "picture": "https://example.com/avatar.png"
  }
}
```

## Implementation Details

### 1. Directory Creation
- Create `.well-known/did/nostr/event/` if it doesn't exist
- Use recursive directory creation
- Handle permissions gracefully

### 2. File Naming
- Use event ID as filename: `<eventid>.json`
- Event IDs are unique, preventing conflicts

### 3. Overwrite Protection
- **Never overwrite existing files**
- Skip saving if file already exists
- Optionally log skipped events (in interactive mode)

### 4. Error Handling
- Handle filesystem permissions errors
- Handle disk space issues
- Graceful fallback when saving fails

### 5. Performance
- Save events asynchronously to avoid blocking
- Use efficient file I/O operations

## Usage Examples

```bash
# Save recent events and exit
agenticchat --save

# Save while watching live stream
agenticchat --save --interactive

# Save with custom event limit
agenticchat --save --max-events 500

# Save without profile data
agenticchat --save --no-profiles
```

## Benefits
- ✅ **Local archiving**: Build permanent local event storage
- ✅ **Offline analysis**: Work with events without network access
- ✅ **Structured storage**: Follows well-known conventions
- ✅ **No overwrites**: Preserves existing data safely
- ✅ **Flexible usage**: Works with all existing CLI modes

## File Structure Example
```
./
├── .well-known/
│   └── did/
│       └── nostr/
│           └── event/
│               ├── abc123def456...json
│               ├── def456ghi789...json
│               └── ghi789jkl012...json
├── events.json  (if using > redirect)
└── ...
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `--save` flag added to CLI argument parsing
- [ ] Directory structure created automatically
- [ ] Events saved as individual JSON files
- [ ] No overwriting of existing files
- [ ] Works with all existing CLI modes (default, interactive, etc.)
- [ ] Profile data included when available
- [ ] Error handling for filesystem issues
- [ ] Updated help text and documentation

- api-change:`ec2`: \[`botocore`] This release adds ModifyInstanceConnectEndpoint API to update configurations on existing EC2 Instance Connect Endpoints and improves IPv6 support through dualstack DNS names for EC2 Instance Connect Endpoints.
- api-change:`endpoint-rules`: \[`botocore`] Update endpoint-rules client to latest version
- api-change:`fsx`: \[`botocore`] Amazon FSx for NetApp ONTAP 2nd generation file systems now support decreasing SSD storage capacity.

- api-change:`qapps`: \[`botocore`] Documentation update for Amazon Q Apps API Reference
- api-change:`servicediscovery`: \[`botocore`] Added support for cross account through Id parameter overloading with ARN and allow owner account for some APIs instead of ARN

<details>
<summary>pallets/click (click)</summary>

### [`v8.2.1`](https://redirect.github.com/pallets/click/blob/HEAD/CHANGES.rst#Version-821)

[Compare Source](https://redirect.github.com/pallets/click/compare/8.2.0...8.2.1)

Released 2025-05-20

- Fix flag value handling for flag options with a provided type. :issue:`2894`
  :issue:`2897` :pr:`2930`
- Fix shell completion for nested groups. :issue:`2906` :pr:`2907`
- Flush `sys.stderr` at the end of `CliRunner.invoke`. :issue:`2682`
- Fix EOF handling for stdin input in CliRunner. :issue:`2787`

### [`v8.2.0`](https://redirect.github.com/pallets/click/blob/HEAD/CHANGES.rst#Version-820)

[Compare Source](https://redirect.github.com/pallets/click/compare/8.1.8...8.2.0)

Released 2025-05-10

- Drop support for Python 3.7, 3.8, and 3.9. :pr:`2588` :pr:`2893`

- Use modern packaging metadata with `pyproject.toml` instead of `setup.cfg`.
  :pr:`2438`

- Use `flit_core` instead of `setuptools` as build backend. :pr:`2543`

- Deprecate the `__version__` attribute. Use feature detection, or
  `importlib.metadata.version("click")`, instead. :issue:`2598`

- `BaseCommand` is deprecated. `Command` is the base class for all
  commands. :issue:`2589`

- `MultiCommand` is deprecated. `Group` is the base class for all group
  commands. :issue:`2590`

- The current parser and related classes and methods, are deprecated.
  :issue:`2205`

  - `OptionParser` and the `parser` module, which is a modified copy of
    `optparse` in the standard library.
  - `Context.protected_args` is unneeded. `Context.args` contains any
    remaining arguments while parsing.
  - `Parameter.add_to_parser` (on both `Argument` and `Option`) is
    unneeded. Parsing works directly without building a separate parser.
  - `split_arg_string` is moved from `parser` to `shell_completion`.

- Enable deferred evaluation of annotations with
  `from __future__ import annotations`. :pr:`2270`

- When generating a command's name from a decorated function's name, the
  suffixes `_command`, `_cmd`, `_group`, and `_grp` are removed.
  :issue:`2322`

- Show the `types.ParamType.name` for `types.Choice` options within
  `--help` message if `show_choices=False` is specified.
  :issue:`2356`

- Do not display default values in prompts when `Option.show_default` is
  `False`. :pr:`2509`

- Add `get_help_extra` method on `Option` to fetch the generated extra
  items used in `get_help_record` to render help text. :issue:`2516`
  :pr:`2517`

- Keep stdout and stderr streams independent in `CliRunner`. Always
  collect stderr output and never raise an exception. Add a new
  output stream to simulate what the user sees in its terminal. Removes
  the `mix_stderr` parameter in `CliRunner`. :issue:`2522` :pr:`2523`

- `Option.show_envvar` now also shows environment variable in error messages.
  :issue:`2695` :pr:`2696`

- `Context.close` will be called on exit. This results in all
  `Context.call_on_close` callbacks and context managers added via
  `Context.with_resource` to be closed on exit as well. :pr:`2680`

- Add `ProgressBar(hidden: bool)` to allow hiding the progressbar. :issue:`2609`

- A `UserWarning` will be shown when multiple parameters attempt to use the
  same name. :issue:`2396`

- When using `Option.envvar` with `Option.flag_value`, the `flag_value`
  will always be used instead of the value of the environment variable.
  :issue:`2746` :pr:`2788`

- Add `Choice.get_invalid_choice_message` method for customizing the
  invalid choice message. :issue:`2621` :pr:`2622`

- If help is shown because `no_args_is_help` is enabled (defaults to `True`
  for groups, `False` for commands), the exit code is 2 instead of 0.
  :issue:`1489` :pr:`1489`

- Contexts created during shell completion are closed properly, fixing
  a `ResourceWarning` when using `click.File`. :issue:`2644` :pr:`2800`
  :pr:`2767`

- `click.edit(filename)` now supports passing an iterable of filenames in
  case the editor supports editing multiple files at once. Its return type
  is now also typed: `AnyStr` if `text` is passed, otherwise `None`.
  :issue:`2067` :pr:`2068`

- Specialized typing of `progressbar(length=...)` as `ProgressBar[int]`.
  :pr:`2630`

- Improve `echo_via_pager` behaviour in face of errors.
  :issue:`2674`

  - Terminate the pager in case a generator passed to `echo_via_pager`
    raises an exception.
  - Ensure to always close the pipe to the pager process and wait for it
    to terminate.
  - `echo_via_pager` will not ignore `KeyboardInterrupt` anymore. This
    allows the user to search for future output of the generator when
    using less and then aborting the program using ctrl-c.

- `deprecated: bool | str` can now be used on options and arguments. This
  previously was only available for `Command`. The message can now also be
  customised by using a `str` instead of a `bool`. :issue:`2263` :pr:`2271`

  - `Command.deprecated` formatting in `--help` changed from
    `(Deprecated) help` to `help (DEPRECATED)`.
  - Parameters cannot be required nor prompted or an error is raised.
  - A warning will be printed when something deprecated is used.

- Add a `catch_exceptions` parameter to `CliRunner`. If
  `catch_exceptions` is not passed to `CliRunner.invoke`, the value
  from `CliRunner` is used. :issue:`2817` :pr:`2818`

- `Option.flag_value` will no longer have a default value set based on
  `Option.default` if `Option.is_flag` is `False`. This results in
  `Option.default` not needing to implement `__bool__`. :pr:`2829`

- Incorrect `click.edit` typing has been corrected. :pr:`2804`

- `Choice` is now generic and supports any iterable value.
  This allows you to use enums and other non-`str` values. :pr:`2796`
  :issue:`605`

- Fix setup of help option's defaults when using a custom class on its
  decorator. Removes `HelpOption`. :issue:`2832` :pr:`2840`

issue.body:
**Claude finished @husams's task** —— [View job](https://github.com/husams/shard-markdown/actions/runs/17021986871)

---
### ✅ **Code Review Completed**

#### Todo List:
- [x] Read repository guidelines (CLAUDE.md)
- [x] Analyze new utils.py module for code quality and implementation
- [x] Review refactored CLI command files for proper consolidation
- [x] Evaluate test coverage and quality
- [x] Check for potential bugs, security issues, and performance concerns
- [x] Provide comprehensive feedback and recommendations

---

### 🔍 **Overall Assessment: EXCELLENT**

This PR demonstrates high-quality refactoring that successfully eliminates code duplication while maintaining backward compatibility. The implementation follows project standards and includes comprehensive test coverage.

### ✅ **Strengths**

1. **Excellent Code Consolidation**
   - Successfully extracted ~44 lines of duplicate code from 4 CLI modules
   - Created clean, reusable utilities in `src/shard_markdown/cli/utils.py:13-56`
   - Single console instance prevents multiple Rich console initialization
   - Consistent error handling across all CLI commands

2. **High-Quality Implementation**
   - Proper type annotations throughout (`src/shard_markdown/cli/utils.py:17-56`)
   - Comprehensive docstrings following Google style
   - Clean exception handling with proper chaining (`src/shard_markdown/cli/utils.py:38`)
   - Follows project's 88-character line length standard

3. **Excellent Test Coverage**
   - 135 lines of comprehensive test code in `tests/unit/cli/test_utils.py`
   - 10 test cases covering all utility functions
   - Tests singleton behavior, error handling, and connection scenarios
   - Proper mocking and exception testing

4. **Clean Refactoring**
   - All 4 CLI files now import from shared utilities
   - Maintains identical functionality - zero breaking changes
   - Removed local console instances and duplicate functions consistently

### ⚠️ **Minor Issues**

1. **Inconsistent String Formatting** (`src/shard_markdown/cli/utils.py:32`)
   ```python
   console.print("[red]Unexpected error:[/red] %s", str(e))
   ```
   Uses printf-style formatting while other messages use f-strings. Consider:
   ```python
   console.print(f"[red]Unexpected error:[/red] {str(e)}")
   ```

2. **Broad Exception Union** (`src/shard_markdown/cli/utils.py:31`)
   The union type `ConnectionError | RuntimeError | ValueError` is quite broad. Consider if this should be more specific to ChromaDB-related exceptions.

### 🔒 **Security Analysis: ✅ SECURE**

- No hardcoded credentials or sensitive data
- Proper exception handling without information leakage
- No user input passed directly to system calls
- No security concerns identified

### ⚡ **Performance Improvements: ✅ POSITIVE**

- **Singleton console instance** reduces object creation overhead
- **Centralized client connection logic** eliminates redundant connection attempts
- **Consistent error handling** reduces code path complexity

### 🧪 **Test Quality: ✅ COMPREHENSIVE**

- **Console singleton test** validates shared instance behavior
- **Error handling tests** cover all exception types and verbosity levels
- **Connection tests** validate success/failure scenarios
- **Proper mocking** without testing implementation details

### 📊 **Architecture Impact: ✅ EXCELLENT**

- Establishes clear separation between CLI infrastructure and command logic
- Creates foundation for future CLI utility expansion
- Improves maintainability through DRY principle
- Consistent error UX across all commands

### 📈 **Code Quality Metrics**

- ✅ **Code reduction:** ~44 lines of duplicate code eliminated
- ✅ **Test coverage:** 135+ lines of comprehensive test coverage added
- ✅ **Type safety:** Full type annotations maintained
- ✅ **Backward compatibility:** 100% maintained
- ✅ **Code style:** Follows all project standards (Black, Ruff, 88 chars)

### 🎯 **Recommendations**

1. **Consider standardizing** string formatting in error messages for consistency
2. **Future enhancement:** Consider extracting common CLI decorators/options to further reduce duplication
3. **Documentation:** The PR description excellently documents the changes and benefits

### 🏆 **Final Verdict: APPROVE**

This is a model refactoring PR that demonstrates:
- Clean code consolidation without functionality changes
- Comprehensive testing of new utilities
- Adherence to project standards and conventions
- Clear documentation of changes and benefits

The minor formatting inconsistency is not a blocker. This PR successfully achieves its goal of eliminating CLI code duplication while maintaining high code quality standards.

---

It is likely that the change in the specified commit of the line
"return "#{APP_VERSION}#";"
to
"return "AudioBookConverter-#{APP_VERSION}#";"
was erroneous

стало ~/.abc/AudioBookConverter-6.5.2
